        "answer_count": 6,
        "title": "How do I specify which constructor of a class I want to call?",
        "body": "<p>I'm creating a defined amount of objects from another class, and attempting to randomize the color for each one using java.awt.Color.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>for (int i = 0; i &lt; numBalls; i++){       \n    ballsInSim.add(\n        new BoxBall(\n            0,\n            0,\n            (int) boxWidth,\n            (int) boxHeight,\n            rng.nextInt(35) + 15,\n            rng.nextInt(500) + 25,\n            rng.nextInt(500) + 25,\n            Color.BLUE, // Create new Colour here using constructor\n            myCanvas\n        )\n    );\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Where <code>Color.BLUE<\/code> currently is, I'd like to call one of Color's constructors that uses three integers for the red, green, and blue values (Color(int r, int g, int b)).<\/p>\n\n<p>How do I call that constructor?  I am relatively new to Java and I'm having some trouble wrapping my head around this. <\/p>\n",
