    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/VEcWG.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 1270277,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1226744,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1226744/leon",
                "reputation": 12521,
                "display_name": "Leon",
                "accept_rate": 69
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1429471353,
            "creation_date": 1429470805,
            "body": "<p>If you call the constructor with the arguments you want the compiler will select the correct one.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 29734572,
            "question_id": 29734546,
            "last_edit_date": 1429471353
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/dcNeu.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 5230417,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 4180965,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4180965/tejjd",
                "reputation": 2569,
                "display_name": "TejjD",
                "accept_rate": 67
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1429471907,
            "creation_date": 1429471348,
            "body": "<p>In order to achieve what you want, simply add the following:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>new Color(0, 0, 255)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>So in essence, it will look like this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>ballsInSim.add(new BoxBall(0, 0, (int) boxWidth, (int) boxHeight, rng.nextInt(35) + 15, rng.nextInt(500) + 25, rng.nextInt(500) + 25, new Color(0, 0, 255), myCanvas));\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>In order to achieve random colors each time:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Random R = new Random(256);\nRandom G = new Random(256);\nRandom B = new Random(256);\n\n//your color constructor will then be:\nnew Color(R.nextInt(), G.nextInt(), B.nextInt());\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>To know more about the Color Class, refer to this: <a href=\"https://www.google.co.za/url?sa=t&amp;rct=j&amp;q=&amp;esrc=s&amp;source=web&amp;cd=1&amp;cad=rja&amp;uact=8&amp;ved=0CBwQFjAA&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fdocs.oracle.com%2Fjavase%2F7%2Fdocs%2Fapi%2Fjava%2Fawt%2FColor.html&amp;ei=XgA0VfuaPJHtauHmgJAC&amp;usg=AFQjCNHPDbAtjIFAA8B3xBzpklmWTbuo9g&amp;sig2=i4-htD-1K0Fn_rmsFtyDiA&amp;bvm=bv.91071109,d.d2s\" rel=\"nofollow\">Color: Java 7<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>Hope this helps<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 29734694,
            "question_id": 29734546,
            "last_edit_date": 1429471907
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/2s35X.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 3093821,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 3182664,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3182664/marco13",
                "reputation": 54835,
                "display_name": "Marco13",
                "accept_rate": 55
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1429472703,
            "creation_date": 1429472703,
            "body": "<p>Regarding the actual question: There are multiple constructors for <code>Color<\/code>. Some of them only differ in the argument type, namely these:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Color(float r, float g, float b)\nColor(int r, int g, int b)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>When you call<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Color c = new Color(r,g,b);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>the question about which constructor will be called is actually a bit tricky: It depends on the type of the given arguments. For details, you may refer to the <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se8/html/jls-15.html#jls-15.9.3\" rel=\"nofollow\">Section 15.9.3. Choosing the Constructor and its Arguments<\/a> of the Java Language Specification. <\/p>\n\n<p>However, in this case, you can make it simple: If you pass in three <code>float<\/code> values, then the <code>float<\/code> version will be called. If you pass in three <code>int<\/code> values, then the <code>int<\/code> version will be called. <\/p>\n\n<p>Concerning the implementation: If your intention is to create random colors, I'd recommend creating a small helper method:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>private static final Random COLOR_RANDOM = new Random(0);\n\nprivate static Color createRandomColor() {\n    int r = COLOR_RANDOM.nextInt(256);\n    int g = COLOR_RANDOM.nextInt(256);\n    int b = COLOR_RANDOM.nextInt(256);\n    return new Color(r,g,b);\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Then, you can simply call this method everywhere, for example...<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>for (int i = 0; i &lt; numBalls; i++)\n{       \n    ballsInSim.add(new BoxBall(0, 0, (int) boxWidth, (int) boxHeight,\n        rng.nextInt(35) + 15, rng.nextInt(500) + 25, rng.nextInt(500) + 25, \n        createRandomColor(),  // &lt;---- ... here!\n        myCanvas));\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 29734970,
            "question_id": 29734546
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/J3ZU1.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 225705,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 486332,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/486332/nana",
                "reputation": 4501,
                "display_name": "nana",
                "accept_rate": 100
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1429473681,
            "creation_date": 1429473681,
            "body": "<p>It's rather simple, Java picks the constructor to use based on the arguments you supply to the constructor. In case of Color you have 7 options as you can see below:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Color(ColorSpace cspace, float[] components, float alpha)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Creates a color in the specified ColorSpace with the color components specified in the float array and the specified alpha.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Color(float r, float g, float b)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Creates an opaque sRGB color with the specified red, green, and blue values in the range (0.0 - 1.0).  <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Color(float r, float g, float b, float a)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Creates an sRGB color with the specified red, green, blue, and alpha values in the range (0.0 - 1.0).<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Color(int rgb)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Creates an opaque <em>sRGB<\/em> color with the specified combined RGB value consisting of the red component in bits 16-23, the green component in bits 8-15, and the blue component in bits 0-7.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Color(int rgba, boolean hasalpha)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Creates an <em>sRGB<\/em> color with the specified combined RGBA value consisting of the alpha component in bits 24-31, the red component in bits 16-23, the green component in bits 8-15, and the blue component in bits 0-7.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Color(int r, int g, int b)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Creates an opaque sRGB color with the specified red, green, and blue values in the range (0 - 255).<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Color(int r, int g, int b, int a)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Creates an <em>sRGB<\/em> color with the specified red, green, blue, and alpha values in the range (0 - 255).  <\/p>\n\n<p>If you supply three <em>ints<\/em>, the last one will be used. In case of three <em>floats<\/em> it will be the third one.<\/p>\n\n<h3>In your case all you have to do is replace <code>Colour.BLUE<\/code> with:<\/h3>\n\n<pre><code>new Colour(\n    new Random().nextInt(256),\n    new Random().nextInt(256),\n    new Random().nextInt(256),\n)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 29735159,
            "question_id": 29734546
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/16ae031def7f1e2adc1b71daac74a28e?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 2112167,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1991295,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1991295/async",
                "reputation": 1537,
                "display_name": "async",
                "accept_rate": 60
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1429471214,
            "creation_date": 1429471214,
            "body": "<p>Assuming you're after <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/awt/Color.html#Color%28float,%20float,%20float%29\" rel=\"nofollow\">this constructor<\/a>, then<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>new Color(r, g, b)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>is instantiating the class using that constructor, where <code>r<\/code>, <code>g<\/code> and <code>b<\/code> are variables / fields that correspond to red, green and blue. <\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 29734665,
            "question_id": 29734546
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8e384344cd7556d1ac9f378cf87e3ff6?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 5480190,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 4356909,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4356909/kuba",
                "reputation": 839,
                "display_name": "Kuba"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1429471441,
            "creation_date": 1429471441,
            "body": "<p>Just do this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>ballsInSim.add(new BoxBall(0, 0, (int) boxWidth, (int) boxHeight, rng.nextInt(35) + 15, rng.nextInt(500) + 25, rng.nextInt(500) + 25, new Color(r, g, b), myCanvas));}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>where <code>r, g, b<\/code> are previously defined random integers from 0 to 255;<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 29734720,
            "question_id": 29734546
        }
    ],
